File: A total of 292,153 tests have been conducted to date with 12,774 tests done in the past 24 hours. JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Health announced the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is 8,232. The number of positive cases have increased by 424. A total of 292,153 tests have been conducted to date with 12,774 tests done in the past 24 hours. WATCH: Gauteng Command Council gives update on COVID-19 The department reported eight more COVID-19-related deaths. Two deaths were reported in KwaZulu-Natal and six in the Western Cape. This brings the total national deaths to 161. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.